Fischer's first tour during the Korean conflict was in F-80s with the 80th Fighter Bomber Squadron &quot;Headhunters.&quot;

His 'battle damage' was most likely from an aggressive pull-up off a bomb run with the 255 gal. 'Misawa' tanks; with the baffling removed, fuel tended to slosh from end to end in the tank, and the load on the mount points in a high &quot;G&quot; environment could prove disastrous... this, by the way, was not an uncommon occurrence.

The airplane, F-80C serial 49-697, had previously been assigned to a sister squadron, the 35th FBS &quot;Panthers&quot; as denoted by the silhouette behind Hal's head. At the outbreak of the war, she had been serving with the 36th FBS... lots of bouncing around.
